=http://www.battle.net/images/battle/diablo2/images/animations/bestiary/act1/Andariel.gif width=175  length=200></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Vox - April 5th, 7 pm PST. Open raid. </span><hr size=1> <br>
I will be holding a Vox raid, Thursday April 5th at 7 PM PST AT Permafrost. Begin to gather at 6:30 PM PST.<br>
<br>
If you would like to attend, please let me know. This is NOT a guild only event, nor is any specific guild sponsoring, funding, or organizing the raid; I am. The rules for attendance will be as follows:<br>
<br>
1) Loot - I will be allocated the first White Dragon Scale if it drops (for bard uber quest). All other items will be randomed for among the primary users of that item, based on who CAN and WILL use it. Example: A cleric CAN and MIGHT use a RBB, but is not the primary user of that item by any means.<br>
<br>
   If you win an item, I'd really appreciate it if you donated cash/items to me to help pay for the raid. <br>
<br>
   The loot can be rolled by the following classes:<br>
      - Crystaline Spear - WAR,RNG, BRD, ROG<br>
      - Dragon Bone Bracer  -  WAR, PAL, RNG, SHD, MNK, BRD, ROG,<br>
      - Mystical Eyepatch - Cleric, sham, druid, ench, necro, wiz, and mage.<br>
      - Kavruul's Mystic Pouch - All classes<br>
      - Rez Stick - Druid, sham, paly, under L45 clerics<br>
      - RBB - Warriors, rogues, monks, rangers, paladins, shadowknights, and bards who are not up for the white scale<br>
      - White dragon scale - Bards (Loot order for this item will be determined by me after discussion with the other bards)<br>
      - Book - Paladins<br>
      - Horn - Bards (Loot order will be decided by bards)<br>
      - Warhammer - Clerics<br>
<br>
   Only those people who are there for the attack will be allowed to roll for loot. Meaning, if you go LD during IGs and never come back... sorry, tough shit. If you go LD during the initial charge, then you can random. If you fall in the pits before the battle (IE go up the wrong ramp), you will not be allowed to random. <br>
<br>
   All gems and cash loot will be given to me to help pay for potions and regents.<br>
<br>
   All loot will be randomed AFTER everyone is rezzed, healed, and ready.  All arguements will be settled by me, and I really don't expect there to be any. <br>
  <br>
2) Cost of compenents - I will be paying for peridots and such. We will be using the good buffs for the assault, and crap jaspers and such for pulling IGs. If you need gems, let me know. All cash/gem loot should be given to me to recoup the cost of these gems. Most tanks will receieve a resist cold potions.<br>
<br>
3) Class/levels - We NEED 3 L50-52 warriors, 3 L49+ clerics, 3 L40+ clerics, 5 L45+ tanks, 4 L45+ enchanters, and 2 L45+ bards (in addition to myself). In addition to those people, we need another 10-20 people, which we will select based primarily on class, level, and CR gear. All classes are welcome. <br>
<br>
4) Gear - Everyone attending is REQUIRED to have a 80 CR, unbuffed, without a potion, and without bard songs. If you're a bard, you may get away with a tad lower, but pretty much everyone must meet this requirement. For resisting, level is very important as well. A L40 with 150 CR will die faster than a L50 with 50 CR. I would suggest that everyone comes with 100+ CR, especially if you plan on doing Vox repeatedly.<br>
<br>
   Easy to get items:<br>
     Gold peridot bracers - AC 3 CR +6 x 2<br>
     Plat peridot rings - AC4 CR +10 x2<br>
     Polar Bear cloak - AC5 +15 CR (easy quest, probably have to pay 20pp for it off a PC)<br>
   Those few easy to get items will pop you upto 72 (Base 25 +12 +20 +15). Add on a few other items and you've got the required CR...<br>
   Other items you should consider getting:<br>
      Crown of the Frog Kings - AC10 CR/FR +20 (good for all dragon raids)<br>
      Icy Greaves (plate classes only) - AC8 CR +5 (drop off elite gobs by king in perma)<br>
      Dwarven ringmail tunic (chain small races) - AC12 MR/CR/FR +8 (probably buyable for under 100pp)<br>
<br>
5) Plan/failure -  Anyone wanting to go, MUST be able to commit 5 hours to the raid. While we may be in and out in 1 hour, PLAN on being there for upto 5 hours. 5 hours is enough time for 2 attempts and a really bad CR.<br>
   A. We will form up groups and clear IGs. Estimated time - 30 minutes. <br>
   B. We will form up buff groups, and buff everyone. Estimated time - 30 minutes. <br>
   C. We will then go over the strategy in the chat room, and form groups. Estimated time - 10 minutes.<br>
   D. We will enter the game, group up, and get ready to attack. Estimated time - 5 minutes MAX.<br>
   E. We will execute our plan, which will primarily consist of 3 "waves". First wave will be "tank and drain". Estimated time - 10 seconds.<br>
      The second wave will be "tank, taunt, drain, and take to 60% life". Estimated time - 20 seconds.<br>
      The third wave will be "nuke and loot". Estimated time - 30 seconds. <br>
   F. If we win - loot and rez. If we fail, we pull corpses, rez, and start over.<br>
   G. After victory, loot will be randomed, and we will exit permafrost through the front door. After EVERYONE leaves the zone, we will port from everfrost. This is to ensure NOONE is left behind.<br>
<br>
   Quick notes. When we buff, you will be sitting at a rock. In front of you are 3 ramps... one to the left as you go forward, another to the left as you go forward, and a ramp straight in front. DO NOT GO UP THE WRONG RAMPS. The 2nd to the left is the correct one. If you don't see people (usually me) standing at the top of the ramp, don't go up it. <br>
   When we are buffed and going to attack... you will go up the 2nd ramp to the left, all the way to the top. Then make a left, and to your right is a secret door with a big boulder in front of it. Click on the big boulder, and a passage will open... that is the way to vox. If you do not understand the above things, you will fall in a trap die, and may have to sit out the whole battle.<br>
<br>
   Our groups will probably consist of -<br>
     i) Primary tank group. 3 best equiped, highest level, fattest warriors. 1 best equiped bard. 1 best equiped cleric, 1 backup well equiped cleric.<br>
     ii) Drain group 1. 4 well equiped enchanters, 2nd best bard, 1 well equiped high mana cleric.<br>
     iii) Drain group 2. Rest of the enchanters, 1 druid, shamy, or cleric.<br>
     iv) Secondary tank group. 3 well equiped tanks/warriors, 3rd best bard, 1 well equiped high mana cleric, 1 lower level cleric with CH. <br>
     v) Tank groups. Have 1 cleric, 1 other healer, and 4 melees.<br>
     vi) Caster groups. Have a cleric or 2 other healers, a few casters, and any leftover tanks.<br>
<br>
To reiterate, if you would like to go, you need to let me know, be of decent level (see above for levels), have a CR of 80 unbuffed, and be able to stay for the whole raid.  I will be given a white dragon scale if it drops, all other loot will be randomed, with everyone only being able to random for 1 item.<br>
<br>
Obviously, I do not expect the white scale to drop on our first try at Vox. Thus, I plan on organizing 2-5 Vox raids, and some Naggy raids if need be.<br>
<br>
If you would like to come, e-mail me at   iutav@aol.com or send me a tell in game. If anyone has any questions, comments or concerns, please let me know.<br>
<br>
-Cueller<br>
